<p>Re: Follow-Up — Potential Unclaimed Funds — Reference {{caseNumber}}</p>

<p>Dear {{claimantFirstName}},</p>

<p>We recently contacted you about potential unclaimed funds (~{{reportedAmount}}) that our research suggests may belong to you. We have not yet heard back from you, so we wanted to follow up.</p>

<p>We understand you may be busy or cautious about this type of communication. We want to assure you:</p>

<p style="padding-left: 20px;">
• <strong>This is not a scam.</strong> We are a licensed surplus recovery service that helps people recover funds they may not know they have.<br>
• <strong>You can verify this independently.</strong> You can look up your name on your state's unclaimed property website to confirm these funds exist.<br>
• <strong>You can file yourself for free.</strong> Our service is optional — we charge {{feePercent}}% only if we successfully recover funds for you.{{#if freeFilingUrl}}<br>
• <strong>File free at:</strong> {{freeFilingUrl}}{{/if}}
</p>

<p>If you would like our help, or if you have any questions, please contact us at {{companyPhone}} or {{companyEmail}} and reference <strong>{{caseNumber}}</strong>.</p>

<p><strong>To stop receiving communications:</strong> Visit {{optOutUrl}}, call {{optOutPhone}}, or write "OPT OUT" to our address above. We will immediately cease contact.</p>

<p>Sincerely,<br>{{companyName}}</p>

<p style="font-size: 9pt; color: #777; margin-top: 30px; border-top: 1px solid #ddd; padding-top: 10px;">
